trend_summary: Successive images show progressive suburban infill: new cul-de-sacs and commercial buildings edge into former woodland, raising roof coverage yet retaining a mostly detached-house pattern. Forest remains dominant in the east but shrinks slightly. Southwest industrial blocks grow, and a fresh sports/recreation complex appears near the wooded fringe.
notable_changes: Gradual infill of detached housing lots along the main north-south corridor.
Expansion of industrial/warehouse roofs in the southwest corner.
Small cul-de-sac subdivisions carved into eastern woodland margin.
Noticeable reduction of contiguous forest edge, especially toward the center-east.
Installation of new sports fields or recreation facilities near the eastern clearing.
